<h1><font color="#7DA647">Milestone : Attribute names being updated</font></h1>
<ul><li><h2>Let there be the universal relation <b>R</b> = {A1, A2, ..., An}.  Any attribute Ak is being updated to Ak'.</h2></li>
<li><h2>This is basically a renaming of the attribute and needs to only be propagated down through the sets <b>F</b>, <b>D</b> and <b>Q</b>.  In this example, by using the relational model notation, we can rename by :</h2></li>
<li><h2><b>ρAk'ΠAk(R)</b></h2></li>
</ul></body>
